description: Released in a span of three months, the new albums by Ayra Starr, Tems and Tyla are not merely career-making for the artists, but ground-shifting for the pop music of the continent.
title: As African pop crests again, women are leading the second wave

description: The game show host was a weatherman in Los Angeles before starting on Wheel of Fortune in 1981.
title: Pat Sajak departs 'Wheel of Fortune' as TV's last old school game show host

description: Morgan Talty's debut novel is a touching narrative about family in which the past and present are constantly on the page as we follow a man's life, while also entertaining what that life could have been.
title: In 'Fire Exit,' a father grapples with connection and the meaning of belonging

description: Glen Powell co-wrote Netflix's Hit Man alongside Richard Linklater, of the Before trilogy. The story is based on a Texas Monthly profile of a real undercover cop.
title: As a fake 'Hit Man,' Glen Powell shows off his real star power

description: More than 150,000 U.S., British and Canadian troops stormed the beaches of Normandy, France, on June 6, 1944. A small handful told NPR about their experience.
title: They were there on D-Day, on the beaches and in the skies. This is what they saw

description: A group of mothers tirelessly search for their missing children and loved ones. They let NPR tag along and shared what they make of the country's recent historic election.
title: About 100,000 people are missing in Mexico. These mothers are trying to find them
